To make sure the website works properly, a few debugging tools were added to help find and fix problems.
A custom debug logger is used to track things like what the user types in, the response from the AI, and any errors that happen.
This makes it easier to see what’s going wrong, especially when the system is trying to get information.
There is also error handling built into the search feature, so if something goes wrong or the user types an invalid term, the website doesn’t crash and instead shows a helpful message.

Another useful feature is the on-screen debug panel, which shows live information like the user’s input, whether the system is loading, any errors, and the result.
This helps a lot during testing because you can see exactly what the website is doing in real time.
There is also a way to track how long the AI takes to respond, which helps check performance.
Overall, these debugging tools make the website more reliable and easier to fix if something goes wrong.
